---
import Layout from '../../components/Layout.astro';
---
<Layout title="Two years at MOE — reflections of an ICT Associate · Victor Ong Jun Qi">
  <main>

    <!-- NAV -->
    <nav style="background:#1a3a5c;padding:0 32px;display:flex;gap:0">
      <a href="/" style="padding:14px 16px;font-size:13px;color:rgba(255,255,255,0.7);text-decoration:none">Home</a>
      <a href="/about" style="padding:14px 16px;font-size:13px;color:rgba(255,255,255,0.7);text-decoration:none">About</a>
      <a href="/blog" style="padding:14px 16px;font-size:13px;color:#fff;text-decoration:none;border-bottom:2px solid #e8a020">Blog</a>
      <a href="/contact" style="padding:14px 16px;font-size:13px;color:rgba(255,255,255,0.7);text-decoration:none">Contact</a>
    </nav>

    <!-- HEADER -->
    <header style="background:#1a3a5c;padding:20px 32px;border-bottom:3px solid #e8a020;display:flex;align-items:center;gap:16px">
      <div style="width:48px;height:48px;border-radius:50%;background:rgba(255,255,255,0.15);display:flex;align-items:center;justify-content:center;font-size:20px;font-weight:500;color:#fff;flex-shrink:0">VO</div>
      <div>
        <div style="color:#fff;font-size:18px;font-weight:500">Victor Ong Jun Qi</div>
        <div style="color:rgba(255,255,255,0.65);font-size:12px">ICT Associate · Ministry of Education / Peicai Secondary School</div>
      </div>
    </header>

    <!-- ARTICLE -->
    <article style="max-width:720px;margin:0 auto;padding:48px 32px">

      <!-- BACK LINK -->
      <a href="/blog" style="font-size:13px;color:#1a3a5c;text-decoration:none;display:inline-flex;align-items:center;gap:6px;margin-bottom:32px">
        ← Back to blog
      </a>

      <!-- META -->
      <div style="display:flex;gap:8px;align-items:center;margin-bottom:16px">
        <span style="font-size:10px;font-weight:500;padding:3px 8px;border-radius:20px;background:#faeeda;color:#633806">Reflection</span>
        <span style="font-size:11px;color:#888">April 2026 · 4 min read</span>
      </div>

      <!-- TITLE -->
      <h1 style="font-size:28px;font-weight:500;color:#1a3a5c;line-height:1.3;margin:0 0 12px">Two years at MOE — reflections of an ICT Associate</h1>

      <!-- AUTHOR -->
      <div style="display:flex;align-items:center;gap:10px;padding:16px 0;border-top:0.5px solid rgba(0,0,0,0.08);border-bottom:0.5px solid rgba(0,0,0,0.08);margin-bottom:32px">
        <div style="width:36px;height:36px;border-radius:50%;background:#1a3a5c;display:flex;align-items:center;justify-content:center;font-size:13px;font-weight:500;color:#fff;flex-shrink:0">VO</div>
        <div>
          <div style="font-size:13px;font-weight:500;color:#1a3a5c">Victor Ong Jun Qi</div>
          <div style="font-size:11px;color:#888">ICT Associate · Peicai Secondary School</div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- BODY -->
      <div style="font-size:15px;color:#333;line-height:1.9">

        <p style="margin:0 0 20px">Two years ago, I stepped into the role of ICT Associate at Peicai Secondary School under the Ministry of Education. At the time, I had a rough idea of what the job entailed — managing ICT infrastructure, supporting teachers with technology, keeping systems running smoothly. What I did not expect was how much more the role would turn out to be.</p>

        <h2 style="font-size:18px;font-weight:500;color:#1a3a5c;margin:32px 0 12px">More than just ICT</h2>
        <p style="margin:0 0 20px">One of the biggest misconceptions about the ICT Associate role is that it is purely technical. In reality, the role spans far beyond ICT. Over the past two years, I have taken on administrative responsibilities, supported colleagues across different departments, and stepped in wherever I was needed. Being part of a school means being part of a community — and that community calls on you in ways no job description can fully capture.</p>

        <h2 style="font-size:18px;font-weight:500;color:#1a3a5c;margin:32px 0 12px">Helping teachers embrace new tools</h2>
        <p style="margin:0 0 20px">Perhaps the most rewarding — and challenging — part of my work has been guiding teachers in adopting new ICT tools. Change is never easy, especially for educators who are already managing packed schedules and demanding workloads. Getting buy-in takes patience, empathy, and a genuine understanding of what teachers need in the classroom. When a teacher tells me that a tool I recommended has made their lessons more engaging, that makes everything worthwhile.</p>

        <h2 style="font-size:18px;font-weight:500;color:#1a3a5c;margin:32px 0 12px">The benefits of working in education</h2>
        <p style="margin:0 0 20px">Working in the education sector comes with its own unique rewards. There is something deeply meaningful about being in an environment where the end goal is the growth and development of young people. The front-facing nature of the role — interacting daily with teachers, students, and staff — keeps the work human and grounded. No two days are the same, and that keeps things fresh.</p>

        <h2 style="font-size:18px;font-weight:500;color:#1a3a5c;margin:32px 0 12px">Looking ahead</h2>
        <p style="margin:0 0 20px">Two years in, I am still learning. The ICT landscape in education is evolving rapidly — AI tools, new platforms, shifting student needs. My role is to stay ahead of those changes and help my school navigate them thoughtfully. I am proud of what I have contributed to both MOE and Peicai Secondary, and I look forward to what the next chapter brings.</p>

        <div style="background:#f0f4f8;border-radius:12px;padding:20px;margin-top:40px;border-left:3px solid #e8a020;border-radius:0">
          <p style="margin:0;font-size:14px;color:#4a6a8a;line-height:1.7;font-style:italic">If you are considering a career as an ICT Associate in MOE, or would like to collaborate on ICT initiatives in education, feel free to <a href="/contact" style="color:#1a3a5c">get in touch</a>.</p>
        </div>

      </div>
    </article>

    <!-- FOOTER -->
    <footer style="background:#1a3a5c;padding:16px 32px;display:flex;justify-content:space-between;align-items:center;margin-top:48px">
      <div style="font-size:11px;color:rgba(255,255,255,0.5)">© 2026 Victor Ong Jun Qi · ICT Associate · Ministry of Education</div>
      <div style="display:flex;gap:16px">
        <a href="/" style="font-size:11px;color:rgba(255,255,255,0.5);text-decoration:none">Home</a>
        <a href="/blog" style="font-size:11px;color:rgba(255,255,255,0.5);text-decoration:none">Blog</a>
        <a href="/contact" style="font-size:11px;color:rgba(255,255,255,0.5);text-decoration:none">Contact</a>
      </div>
    </footer>

  </main>
</Layout>
